.com/k4XiF7UoB6EVlIam0PPE2BkLU0g=/375x500/6a16862d-52ff-4aa6-9da3-ce7f827176d1--Casa_Polanco_Exterior.jpg, https://images.food52.com/iQR2yz1GZylrQZ2q5iof8EpTbOk=/750x1000/6a16862d-52ff-4aa6-9da3-ce7f827176d1--Casa_Polanco_Exterior.jpg 2x\" alt=\"\" width=\"964\" height=\"1285\" data-expand=\"750\" data-srcset=\"https://images.food52.com/k4XiF7UoB6EVlIam0PPE2BkLU0g=/375x500/6a16862d-52ff-4aa6-9da3-ce7f827176d1--Casa_Polanco_Exterior.jpg, https://images.food52.com/iQR2yz1GZylrQZ2q5iof8EpTbOk=/750x1000/6a16862d-52ff-4aa6-9da3-ce7f827176d1--Casa_Polanco_Exterior.jpg 2x\"/\u003e\u003c/picture\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n    \u003c/div\u003e\n\n  \u003c/figure\u003e\n\n              \u003ch4\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.casapolanco.com/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eCasa Polanco\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/h4\u003e\n              \u003cp\u003eOne of my favorite properties in CDMX, Casa Polanco, is a hotel built from a restored mansion. Located just across from the park, it has a darling boutique feel, nestled behind wrought iron gates with a paleta cart in the courtyard. The rooms themselves strike a balance between modern and historic charm—think clean, white interiors with intricate wrought iron window details. FYI:with just eight rooms it’s usually booked out months in advance.\u003c/p\u003e\n              \n\n  \u003cfigure\u003e\n    \u003cdiv\u003e\n      \u003ca href=\"https://www.pinterest.com/pin/create/button\" data-pin-do=\"buttonPin\" data-pin-media=\"\" data-pin-custom=\"true\" data-ga-event=\"inPageInteraction\" data-ga-event-action=\"Pinterest Share\" data-ga-event-label=\"Article Body Image\" data-ga-destination-url=\"none\"\u003e\n        \u003csvg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 16.9 20.8\"\u003e\u003cpath d=\"M16.8 6.3C16.5 3.2 13.6.4 10.1.1 4.8-.5.1 2.7 0 7.9c0 2.4.8 4 2.9 4.8 1.5-1.5-.3-2.4-.5-4C2 4.3 7.1.1 11.7 2.9c3.2 1.9 2.6 9.9-1.2 10.7-.8.1-1.8-.1-2.1-.5-1.9-1.8 1.5-4.8.4-7.3-.9-2.1-3.6-.4-3.9 1.5-.2 1 .3 2 .3 2.9 0 2.1-1.3 5-1.7 7.1-.2.9-.3 